<hl>
<seg id=1> Guangxi made use of US$150 million foreign capital for the basic facilities of water transport. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Nanling, 14 March by Lu Hankui According to the Department of Traffic in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, so far Guangxi had made use of US$150 million from the World Bank, the Asian Bank, Holland, South Korea, etc for the basic facilities of water transport. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In recent years, located in the southwest of China, the construction of the Big Channel to the ocean passing through Guangxi were going on at an accelerated pace. </seg>
<seg id=4> In order to solve the problem of inadequate funds, and to widen the level of open policy, Guangxi devoted major efforts to introducing foreign capital. </seg>
<seg id=5> The second-term of Xijiang Key Shipping Project was invested more than 2 billion Yuan of which US$80 million was the loan from the World Bank. Now 80% of the main excavation finished, so did 50% of concrete pouring. </seg>
<seg id=6> The second-term project of Fangcheng Habor City (including the expressway from Qinzhou City to Fangcheng Habor City) made use of US$52 million loan from the Asian Development Bank. It's estimated that the expressway would be completed and put into operation in the later half of the year. </seg>
<seg id=7> The construction project of Beihai Harbor Conveyance System made use of US$10 million loan from Korean government. </seg>
<seg id=8> The construction project of Qinzhou Harbor Conveyance System made use of US$13 million loan from Holland government. </seg>
<seg id=9> All these projects were advancing smoothly. </seg>
</p>
